Africa’s richest man, Aliko Dangote has said that he tested negative for COVID-19. Dangote disclosed this via his verified Twitter handle on Sunday. He tweeted, “The COVID-19 pandemic has significantly disrupted modern society, affecting our collective health and well-being. “As a global citizen and business leader, I took the COVID-19 test and the result came back NEGATIVE. “Coalition against COVID-19 is an initiative that I am leading with other private sector leaders & our common goal is to support ongoing Government initiatives with our resources in the fight against COVID-19. “We are in this together and I am optimistic we will overcome.”